# Optional Git LFS support for model weights.
#
# MATs does NOT commit the checkpoints to this public repo by default -- they are
# hosted on Hugging Face and fetched with `mats fetch-weights` (see docs/weights.md).
# Committing the 2.65 GB BiRefNet checkpoint here would force every `git clone` to
# download it and would spend the repo's LFS bandwidth quota.
#
# This rule only takes effect if you deliberately place weights under weights/ and
# commit them (e.g. in a private mirror). It is inert otherwise.
weights/*.pth filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
